                    </div>
                    <span>What would it be like to live in North America before Columbus?  You get an idea of how beautiful our country was before industry and population changed it all forever.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">New England, a tamed, emasculated country</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>1</span>
                      /
                      <span>1</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-06-22</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This is a ecological history of New England from 1633 to 1855.  What began as heavily forested land abundant with wildlife, was slowly and inexorably domesticated and exploited.  By the 1840s, Henry David Thoreau comments that New England is now a tamed, emasculated country.  What would he think of New England today?</span>
                  
              
